orig=Winds for three last days SE SW WSW to SW to SSW. On 30 the 7 AM wind to NE following heavy with snow and sleet and veered by N 9 AM NW with large amounts of snow and some drift. Roads now good for sleighing. Weather mild. Has this snow storm here any cause and what connection with the Rocky Mountain & Missouri snow storm (as per telegram). I am strangely impressed that the storm was a nasty cyclone mno|Local time: daily|QC flag: None|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-11-01_OBS-L.jpg
orig=Unusual high tide no damage or danger. [Illegible] also the appearance before the snow storm mno|Local time: daily|QC flag: None|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-11-01_OBS-L.jpg

orig=Prevailing winds NW to SW and S and SE back again then W to NW same as last year. High winds and heavy squalls and damp. This variable nature of the winds is an interesting co-existing fact with the apparent position of the Milky Way and leads me to conclude prima fascie at all events for a similar season (the rest seems to be astronomical observations). mno|Local time: daily|QC flag: None|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-12-01_OBS-L.jpg

orig=8 days partial rain this month. These times very uncertain but frequently every late at night or every early in the morning. mno|Local time: daily|QC flag: None|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-12-01_OBS-L.jpg

orig=The cumulus cloud of mixed gray leaden and yellow colour is very fine about here often. In the fine days the cirrus is scattered in its beautiful form about the heavens. The amount of cloudiness in december was very great but I can give no exact idea of cloud, save that it poured down as rain often and then it froze on New Years night so that there was nothing but a glitter of ice as a huge shaking throughout the whole town. mno|Local time: daily|QC flag: None|Image File: HarbourGrace_USSI-401_M1958_1871-12-01_OBS-L.jpg
